This project is based on academic laboratory experiments developed for:

ICT-4110 – Cryptography and Network Security Laboratory
Islamic University, Bangladesh

This project includes implementations of classical and modern cryptographic algorithms
such as Caesar Cipher, Playfair Cipher, Hill Cipher, Vigenère Cipher, Rail Fence Cipher,
RSA, and Diffie-Hellman.

Some parts of this project were adapted and refactored from previous academic work:
https://github.com/SajjadHossainSoykot/ICT-4110-Cryptography-and-Network-Security-Laboratory

Modifications:
- Converted standalone scripts into REST API (FastAPI/Flask)
- Structured backend for web integration
- Designed for frontend integration using Next.js
- Improved modularity and usability

This project is intended for educational purposes only.